ce:section.ce:para:
The findings were subjected to further Grey Relational Analysis (GRA) in order to determine the most significant factor and the optimal combination of input parameters for reduced corrosion rates. In this study, all of the responses are taken into consideration and the greater the better concept for hardness, the smaller the better concept for surface roughness and porosity for applied for normalizing. Each individual response's Grey relationship grade was determined and shown in Table 5
                        . The larger the better concept was applied for Grade analysis. The response table (Table 6
                        ) and main effect plots (Fig. 3
                        ) were generated based on the computed Grey relational grade in order to determine the optimal level values. Particle size 50 μm, spray distance 100 mm, and feed rate 100 g/min were found to be optimum conditions based on the response table and main effects plot. Following the application of this optimum coating, samples were subjected to mechanical characterization and corrosion analysis.
